From: Performance Patch Series
Subject: [PATCH 09/10] Batch INFORMATION_SCHEMA queries per dataset

Bottleneck #1 (N+1 queries): GetColumnSchema and GetConstraintSchema
issue one INFORMATION_SCHEMA query per table. For a dataset with N
tables, this produces N+1 queries (1 for TABLES, N for COLUMNS) plus
additional constraint queries.

This patch introduces a batch approach:
- Fetch ALL columns for the dataset in one query (with optional
  columnNamePattern filter), then partition results in memory by
  table_name.
- Fetch ALL table constraints for the dataset in one query, then
  partition by table_name.
- KEY_COLUMN_USAGE and CONSTRAINT_COLUMN_USAGE remain per-constraint
  queries (few constraints per table makes this acceptable).

This reduces the column query count from O(N) to O(1) per dataset
and constraint query count from O(N) to O(1) per dataset, which
dramatically reduces latency for datasets with many tables.

The pre-fetched data is passed to the existing builder methods as
dictionaries keyed by table name, avoiding changes to the Arrow
array construction logic.

